```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "resource_manager": "Slurm",
    "partition": "gpu",
    "cores": 18,
    "gpus": 4,
    "memory": "20G",
    "time_limit": "1-00:00:00",
    "account": "pi_dhruveshpate_umass_edu",
    "environment": "miniconda/22.11.1-1",
    "conda_environment": "harness",
    "executable": "/work/pi_dhruveshpate_umass_edu/vdorna_umass_edu/SmallLMReasoning/eval-scripts/phi2-gsm8k.sh" 
  }
}
```

This script uses Slurm as the resource manager and submits a job to the "gpu" partition. It requests 18 cores, 4 GPUs, 20 GB of memory, and a time limit of 1 hour. It also uses the miniconda environment version 22.11.1-1 and activates the "harness" conda environment. Finally, it runs the bash script "phi2-gsm8k.sh" located in the directory "/work/pi_dhruveshpate_umass_edu/vdorna_umass_edu/SmallLMReasoning/eval-scripts".
